The couple, who are both aged 20, were arrested in the southern border town of Beitbridge, it said. The pair have reportedly appeared before a magistrate where they were charged with publishing or communicating a false statement prejudicial to the State. It is unclear if they were asked to plea. The Government says Mnangagwa is on his three-week annual break, returning to work at the end of the month. He missed Tuesday's burials of two Cabinet Ministers who both died of coronavirus. --BBC--